<TITLE> Govt to fix micro credit interest </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Apr 05 (bdnews24.com)  The government will fix a reasonable interest rate for micro credit, said the finance minister on Monday. AMA Muhith told the parliament that, in collaboration with Transparency International Bangladesh, the government would fix a new rate, responding to a query from Naogaon-2 Mp Sahiduzzaman Sarker. The minister also said that the government had already asked micro credit organisations to limit their interest rate below 30 percent. Answering to a written question from Chittagong-10 MP M Abdul Latif, Muhith said the National Bureau of Revenue was conducting special drives to prevent income tax evasion. Muhith also said in parliament that a survey is going to be initiated to identify new taxpayers. The government is also considering to restructure the income tax department to expand its network at the upazila level. Replying to another query from Netrakona-1 MP Moshtaq Ahmed Ruhee, Muhith said that interests of about Tk 3 crore were written off between 2001 and 2008 of more than one crore loan-defaulters across the country. Telecommunication minister Raziuddin Ahmed Razu, replying to MP Begum Faridunnahar Lailee's question, said the Bangladesh Telecommunication Regulatory Corporation had earned a revenue of Tk 1138.69 crore so far in the current fiscal. bdnew
